<unload unload_date="2025-01-01 00:00:00">
<sys_ui_policy action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
    <active>true</active>
    <conditions>party_typeISNOTEMPTY^ORparty_typeISEMPTY^EQ</conditions>
    <description>Polymorphic field-rendering UI Policy on x_casemgmt_case_party. Implements the ServiceNow-native equivalent of ArkCase's @DiscriminatorColumn(cm_class_name) single-table inheritance pattern from PersonAssociation.java and the dual-table @ManyToOne pattern from PersonOrganizationAssociation.java per AAP Section 0.4.3 ("Polymorphic association via single-table choice + UI Policy"). Uses run_scripts=true with an imperative onCondition script to deterministically set field visibility and mandatory state for all three party_type values: "Person" (show person + mandatory; hide organization), "Organization" (show organization + mandatory; hide person), and empty (hide both fields, both not mandatory). The script_true block is the sole logic path; no declarative actions are used because the declarative two-policy approach with reverse_if_false=true has an unavoidable order-conflict in the empty-state case. Runs on form load (on_load=true) so existing case_party records render correctly when opened. The party_type field itself is mandatory at the dictionary level (../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_party_party_type.xml), so users cannot save a record without picking one; the mandatory state of person/organization is therefore conditional on party_type and enforced ONLY through this UI Policy.</description>
    <global>true</global>
    <inherit>false</inherit>
    <name>Case Party Conditional Fields</name>
    <on_load>true</on_load>
    <order>100</order>
    <reverse_if_false>false</reverse_if_false>
    <run_scripts>true</run_scripts>
    <script_false/>
    <script_true><![CDATA[function onCondition() {
    // ServiceNow-native equivalent of ArkCase's @DiscriminatorColumn pattern
    // from PersonAssociation.java. The party_type Choice field acts as the
    // discriminator that drives which reference field is shown and required.
    // Replaces the dual JPA entities (PersonAssociation, PersonOrganizationAssociation)
    // with a single ServiceNow polymorphic table per AAP Section 0.4.3.
    var partyType = g_form.getValue('party_type');
    if (partyType === 'Person') {
        // Show person reference field, make it mandatory; hide organization.
        // The 'Person' string literal MUST match the case-sensitive label
        // declared in ../choices/sys_choice_case_party_party_type.xml byte-for-byte.
        g_form.setDisplay('person', true);
        g_form.setMandatory('person', true);
        g_form.setDisplay('organization', false);
        g_form.setMandatory('organization', false);
    } else if (partyType === 'Organization') {
        // Show organization reference field, make it mandatory; hide person.
        // The 'Organization' string literal MUST match the case-sensitive label
        // declared in ../choices/sys_choice_case_party_party_type.xml byte-for-byte.
        g_form.setDisplay('person', false);
        g_form.setMandatory('person', false);
        g_form.setDisplay('organization', true);
        g_form.setMandatory('organization', true);
    } else {
        // party_type is empty (new record before user picks). Hide both fields
        // and clear mandatory overrides so user is not blocked from saving
        // a half-filled record. The party_type field itself is mandatory at
        // the dictionary level so the user cannot save without selecting one
        // (per ../dictionary/x_casemgmt_case_party_party_type.xml).
        g_form.setDisplay('person', false);
        g_form.setMandatory('person', false);
        g_form.setDisplay('organization', false);
        g_form.setMandatory('organization', false);
    }
}]]></script_true>
    <short_description>Polymorphic field rendering: show person+mandatory when party_type=Person, show organization+mandatory when party_type=Organization, hide both when party_type is empty.</short_description>
